12:33.834 --> 12:36.069
HEY, HEY.

12:36.069 --> 12:38.004
I'M SORRY
I YELLED AT YOU.

12:38.004 --> 12:43.309
♪♪♪♪

12:43.309 --> 12:45.345
YOU DID THE RIGHT THING.

12:45.345 --> 12:47.848
YOU KNOW, ANYTHING HE SAYS
COULD SET HIM BACK.

12:47.848 --> 12:49.850
THAT'S STILL WYATT'S FATHER.

12:49.850 --> 12:52.085
AND IT'S STILL A SOURCE
OF GREAT PAIN FOR HIM.

12:52.085 --> 12:55.021
BE THAT AS IT MAY,
HE LOVES HIS SON,

12:55.021 --> 12:58.158
AND HE NEEDS TO SEE HIM.

12:58.158 --> 13:00.667
HOW ARE <i>YOU?</i>

13:00.667 --> 13:02.435
HOW AM I?

13:02.435 --> 13:06.039
I'M ‐‐ I'M FINE...
I GUESS.

13:06.039 --> 13:07.908
HOW'S MELISSA?

13:07.908 --> 13:09.910
THAT GIRL NEEDS HELP, DAD.

13:09.910 --> 13:13.213
SHE'S DEPRESSED
AND SUICIDAL.

13:13.213 --> 13:15.616
WHAT DID YOUR MOTHER
DO TO HER?

13:17.718 --> 13:21.254
EVERYTHING.
EVERYTHING.

13:21.254 --> 13:22.923
BUT I THINK THE THING
THAT SET HER OFF

13:22.923 --> 13:26.126
WAS THAT HER DAD DIED.

13:26.126 --> 13:27.894
OH, I'M SORRY
TO HEAR THAT.

13:27.894 --> 13:30.897
I KNEW HIM.

13:30.897 --> 13:32.799
YOU KNEW HIM?
YES, YES.

13:32.799 --> 13:35.135
YOUR MOTHER AND I
WERE FRIENDS WITH THEM

13:35.135 --> 13:37.771
FOR YEARS, AND...YEAH.

13:37.771 --> 13:40.707
OH. OKAY.

13:40.707 --> 13:43.644
SO, WHAT IS IT YOU WANTED
TO TALK TO ME ABOUT?

13:43.644 --> 13:46.947
♪♪♪♪

13:46.947 --> 13:50.283
I WAS TOLD YOU HAD SOMETHING
TO DO WITH QUINCY'S MURDER.

13:50.283 --> 13:54.521
♪♪♪♪

13:54.521 --> 13:57.524
DAD,
HE'S A HORRIBLE PERSON.

13:57.524 --> 13:59.059
I KNOW THAT.

13:59.059 --> 14:06.372
♪♪♪♪

14:06.372 --> 14:07.908
WHAT HAPPENED?

14:07.908 --> 14:11.912
♪♪♪♪

14:11.912 --> 14:15.749
I DIDN'T MEAN TO.
UM...

14:15.749 --> 14:17.584
JEFFERY.

14:19.553 --> 14:20.621
TELL ME.

14:20.621 --> 14:23.489
♪♪♪♪

14:23.489 --> 14:25.892
IT'S...

14:25.892 --> 14:28.829
IT'S LIKE IT ALL HAPPENED
IN SLOW MOTION.

14:31.297 --> 14:33.534
THIS IS KIND OF HARD
FOR ME TO...

14:33.534 --> 14:36.202
OKAY, ALL RIGHT,
ALL RIGHT.

14:36.202 --> 14:39.139
TAKE YOUR TIME.

14:39.139 --> 14:40.974
I WALKED INTO
CANDACE'S HOUSE,

14:40.974 --> 14:45.746
AND, UM...
HE WAS BEATING HER.

14:45.746 --> 14:50.984
SO I GRABBED A VASE AND I ‐‐
AND I HIT HIM WITH IT.

14:50.984 --> 14:55.989
AND ‐‐ AND THEN
HE GOT UP, AND HE, UH...

14:55.989 --> 14:58.792
HE STARTED HITTING ME.

14:58.792 --> 15:01.735
♪♪♪♪

15:01.735 --> 15:03.870
I JUST GOT MAD.

15:05.939 --> 15:09.242
AND THE NEXT THING I KNOW,

15:09.242 --> 15:13.279
I WAS ON THE FLOOR
AND I WAS COVERED IN BLOOD.

15:13.279 --> 15:17.150
♪♪♪♪

15:17.150 --> 15:21.655
REMEMBER, DID YOU ‐‐
DID YOU STAB HIM?

15:21.655 --> 15:22.823
YES.

15:22.823 --> 15:27.227
♪♪♪♪

15:27.227 --> 15:29.362
SO, YOUR MOTHER
KNOWS ABOUT THIS?

15:29.362 --> 15:31.932
YEAH.

15:31.932 --> 15:33.800
JEFFERY, WHY DID YOU
BRING THIS TO HER?

15:33.800 --> 15:35.168
WHY DIDN'T YOU COME TO ME?

15:35.168 --> 15:37.170
I DIDN'T BRING IT TO HER, DAD.
SHE FOUND OUT.

15:37.170 --> 15:38.171
HOW?

15:38.171 --> 15:40.741
I DON'T KNOW.

15:40.741 --> 15:44.244
WHY DIDN'T YOU
CALL THE POLICE?

15:44.244 --> 15:46.446
CANDACE SAID IT WAS
A CRIME OF PASSION

15:46.446 --> 15:48.749
AND THEY WOULD
ARREST US FOR MURDER.

15:48.749 --> 15:50.083
THAT CRIMINAL ‐‐

15:52.418 --> 15:54.755
YOU SHOULD'VE CALLED ME.

15:54.755 --> 15:56.690
I DIDN'T WANT
TO GET YOU INVOLVED.

15:56.690 --> 15:58.424
YOU'RE MY SON.
I KNOW.

15:58.424 --> 16:00.360
I'M ALREADY INVOLVED
IN ANYTHING YOU DO.

16:00.360 --> 16:02.769
I'M SORRY.
I'M SORRY.

16:02.769 --> 16:06.039
AND YOU BURIED HIM
IN THE BACKYARD. THAT'S ‐‐

16:06.039 --> 16:09.576
SHE WANTED
TO TAKE THE BODY OUT,

16:09.576 --> 16:11.077
BUT WE COULDN'T,

16:11.077 --> 16:14.014
BECAUSE THE NEXT‐DOOR NEIGHBOR,
SHE HAD CAMERAS AT HER HOUSE.

16:14.014 --> 16:19.586
♪♪♪♪

16:19.586 --> 16:25.125
SO...THIS IS WHAT
YOUR MOTHER HAS ON YOU?

16:25.125 --> 16:26.392
YEAH.

16:26.392 --> 16:29.129
OKAY.

16:29.129 --> 16:31.064
I JUST WISH
YOU WOULD'VE TOLD ME.

16:33.299 --> 16:36.537
I MEAN, I THINK IT'S ‐‐
IT'S GOING TO BE OKAY.

16:36.537 --> 16:39.573
HOW CAN YOU
POSSIBLY THINK THAT?

16:39.573 --> 16:41.975
SHE SAID THAT SHE'S GOING
TO GO TO THE COURT TOMORROW

16:41.975 --> 16:45.345
AND HAVE THE DISCOVERY
OF THE BODY THROWN OUT.

16:45.345 --> 16:48.014
SHE CAN'T JUST
HAVE IT THROWN OUT.

16:48.014 --> 16:49.349
SHE SAYS THAT, YOU KNOW,

16:49.349 --> 16:51.785
THEY WERE ISSUING
A WARRANT IN CANDACE'S NAME,

16:51.785 --> 16:54.120
BUT AT THE TIME
THAT THEY FOUND THE BODY,

16:54.120 --> 16:57.323
THE HOUSE WAS
IN THE BANK'S NAME.

16:57.323 --> 17:00.827
SHE MIGHT BE ABLE
TO PULL THAT OFF.

17:00.827 --> 17:03.870
IF SHE DOES,
THERE'S NO BODY,

17:03.870 --> 17:07.407
THEY'RE GOING TO BE
LOOKING FOR WITNESSES.

17:07.407 --> 17:10.376
NOW, WHO ELSE KNOWS
THAT YOU WERE INVOLVED?

17:10.376 --> 17:14.480
JUST CANDACE...
UM...MOM...

17:14.480 --> 17:19.385
AND BENNY,
CANDACE'S BROTHER.

17:19.385 --> 17:20.654
OKAY.

17:22.956 --> 17:26.026
I'M GOING TO GET YOU
OUT OF THIS ‐‐ ALL OF IT.

17:26.026 --> 17:29.029
♪♪♪♪

17:29.029 --> 17:30.564
HOW?

17:30.564 --> 17:33.099
GO HOME, OKAY?

17:33.099 --> 17:34.467
GO WHERE? MOM'S?

17:34.467 --> 17:36.603
NO, TO YOUR PLACE.

17:36.603 --> 17:39.472
YEAH, BUT SHE
MOVED ME OUT, REMEMBER?

17:39.472 --> 17:41.341
RIGHT, OKAY. JUST...

17:41.341 --> 17:43.043
GO GET A ROOM
AT A HOTEL AND ‐‐

17:43.043 --> 17:46.747
AND CALL ME,
AND I'LL WORK SOMETHING OUT.

17:46.747 --> 17:48.915
ALL RIGHT.
ALL RIGHT.

17:48.915 --> 17:51.484
♪♪♪♪

17:51.484 --> 17:55.722
SON, IT'S GOING
TO BE ALL RIGHT.

17:55.722 --> 17:57.423
IT IS.

17:57.423 --> 17:58.659
THANKS.

18:01.234 --> 18:02.536
ALL RIGHT.

18:02.536 --> 18:08.775
♪♪♪♪

18:15.381 --> 18:19.085
♪♪♪♪

18:19.085 --> 18:20.921
MR. CRYER, NO?

18:23.557 --> 18:25.058
YES. WHO ARE YOU?

18:25.058 --> 18:27.160
HI. I'M ANNA.

18:27.160 --> 18:28.895
NICE MEETING YOU.

18:28.895 --> 18:30.230
AND WHO ARE YOU?

18:30.230 --> 18:34.367
UM, I RUN THE REHAB PROGRAM
THAT HE SIGNED HIMSELF INTO.

18:34.367 --> 18:35.401
OH.

18:39.172 --> 18:40.574
HI.

18:40.574 --> 18:42.709
HOW'S HE DOING?

18:42.709 --> 18:46.146
WELL, WE JUST ‐‐
REALLY, HOW IS HE DOING?

18:46.146 --> 18:47.781
LIKE I WAS SAYING,
WE JUST STARTED TONIGHT,

18:47.781 --> 18:50.917
SO I CAN'T REALLY
TELL YOU, BUT...

18:50.917 --> 18:52.686
ALL I CAN SAY
IS THAT HE'S STRONG

18:52.686 --> 18:54.054
AND LET ME TELL YOU

18:54.054 --> 18:57.924
THAT HE'S REALLY
TRYING TO DETOX.

18:57.924 --> 19:00.393
I NEED A FEW MINUTES
ALONE WITH MY SON, PLEASE.

19:00.393 --> 19:04.638
MR. CRYER, I DON'T THINK
THAT'S A GOOD IDEA.

19:04.638 --> 19:06.106
ANNA, IS IT? ANNA?

19:06.106 --> 19:08.274
YEAH, IT'S ANNA.

19:08.274 --> 19:10.511
I HAVEN'T SEEN MY SON
IN A VERY LONG TIME,

19:10.511 --> 19:13.113
AND I NEED TO SPEND
A FEW MOMENTS

19:13.113 --> 19:14.447
ALONE WITH HIM, PLEASE.

19:14.447 --> 19:16.182
YEAH, I UNDERSTAND,
BUT HE'S SLEEPING,

19:16.182 --> 19:17.751
AND THAT'S A GOOD THING.

19:17.751 --> 19:19.252
IT TOOK US A WHILE
TO GET HIM THERE, SO ‐‐

19:19.252 --> 19:20.554
I WON'T WAKE HIM UP.

19:20.554 --> 19:22.756
OKAY, BUT IF HE WAKES UP
AND SEES YOU, HE'S GOING TO ‐‐

19:22.756 --> 19:25.726
I KNOW.

19:25.726 --> 19:28.762
YOU DON'T WANT HIM
TO GET AGITATED. I GET IT.

19:28.762 --> 19:33.399
HE'S REALLY TRYING TO GET
THROUGH THIS, SO...NO.

19:33.399 --> 19:36.036
LOOK, I UNDERSTAND,
AND I KNOW I CAN BE ABRASIVE,

19:36.036 --> 19:39.339
BUT WOULD YOU PLEASE GIVE ME
JUST A LITTLE BIT OF TIME?

19:39.339 --> 19:43.009
I'LL JUST GIVE YOU A SECOND.
I'LL ‐‐ I'LL BE OUTSIDE.

19:43.009 --> 19:44.377
THANK YOU.

19:44.377 --> 19:54.387
♪♪♪♪

19:54.387 --> 20:04.337
♪♪♪♪

20:04.337 --> 20:14.347
♪♪♪♪

20:14.347 --> 20:24.357
♪♪♪♪

20:24.357 --> 20:34.367
♪♪♪♪

20:34.367 --> 20:41.875
♪♪♪♪

20:41.875 --> 20:45.111
♪♪♪♪

20:45.111 --> 20:47.614
YOU GOT THIS, BUDDY.

20:47.614 --> 20:51.785
♪♪♪♪

20:51.785 --> 20:53.820
[ DOOR OPENS ]

20:57.858 --> 21:01.034
OH. I, UM...

21:01.034 --> 21:03.637
I'M SORRY I, UH...

21:03.637 --> 21:05.038
ARE YOU SURE
HE'S GOING TO BE OKAY?

21:05.038 --> 21:09.810
MR. CRYER, ALL I CAN TELL YOU
IS THAT HE HAS TO WANT IT.

21:09.810 --> 21:11.244
HONESTLY,
I THINK HE DOES,

21:11.244 --> 21:15.616
SO LET'S SEE WHAT HAPPENS
IN THE NEXT FEW WEEKS, OKAY?

21:15.616 --> 21:18.484
HE'S ALL I HAVE LEFT
IN THE WORLD.

21:18.484 --> 21:21.154
UM...
DO YOU HAVE A CARD?

21:21.154 --> 21:22.723
HAVE A WAY I CAN GET
IN TOUCH WITH YOU?

21:22.723 --> 21:25.325
YEAH, SURE.

21:25.325 --> 21:27.561
OKAY, I'LL CALL YOU
AND I WILL GIVE YOU ‐‐

21:27.561 --> 21:29.062
I'LL GIVE YOU
ALL OF MY NUMBERS.

21:29.062 --> 21:31.364
THANK YOU.
OKAY.

21:31.364 --> 21:33.834
ALL RIGHT, AND YOU HAVE TO HAVE
SOMEBODY WATCH HIM IN THIS ROOM.

21:33.834 --> 21:35.101
YEAH, WE'VE WORKED
WITH A LOT OF PEOPLE,

21:35.101 --> 21:36.336
SO WE KNOW ALL THE TRICKS.

21:36.336 --> 21:37.671
I UNDERSTAND YOU WORKED
WITH A LOT OF PEOPLE,

21:37.671 --> 21:40.874
BUT HE IS VERY GOOD AT MAKING
PEOPLE THINK HE'S CLEAN.

21:40.874 --> 21:43.209
MR. CRYER,
HE'S IN THE BEST HANDS.

21:43.209 --> 21:44.745
OKAY? I ASSURE YOU.

21:44.745 --> 21:45.746
THANK YOU.

21:45.746 --> 21:47.614
NO PROBLEM.

21:47.614 --> 21:49.816
IT WAS NICE MEETING YOU.

21:49.816 --> 21:50.917
THANKS.

21:50.917 --> 21:57.223
♪♪♪♪

21:57.223 --> 22:04.938
♪♪♪♪

22:09.876 --> 22:12.579
HANNA?

22:12.579 --> 22:13.947
HEY.

22:13.947 --> 22:15.882
MORNING.

22:15.882 --> 22:17.951
THOUGHT YOU'D
STILL BE ASLEEP.

22:17.951 --> 22:20.020
HOW DO YOU FEEL?

22:20.020 --> 22:22.388
I DON'T KNOW.

22:22.388 --> 22:25.659
DID THAT PILL WORK?

22:25.659 --> 22:28.629
FOR ABOUT AN HOUR,
I GUESS.

22:28.629 --> 22:32.198
HANNA, HAVE YOU
BEEN UP ALL NIGHT?

22:32.198 --> 22:33.700
IT'S ALL RIGHT.

22:33.700 --> 22:35.769
OHH.

22:35.769 --> 22:37.971
COME ON IN THE KITCHEN.
LET'S GET YOU SOME BREAKFAST.

22:37.971 --> 22:39.906
I CAN'T EAT NOTHING.

22:39.906 --> 22:43.443
HANNA, YOU HAVE
TO EAT SOMETHING.

22:43.443 --> 22:46.246
I'M OKAY.

22:46.246 --> 22:49.182
WELL...

22:49.182 --> 22:50.984
I KNOW I CAN'T FORCE YOU.

22:53.186 --> 22:57.023
THIS MORNING, I WAS WONDERING
WHAT I WAS GOING TO SAY TO YOU.

22:57.023 --> 23:01.027
THEN I REALIZED
THERE'S NOTHING TO SAY.

23:01.027 --> 23:03.136
TRUTH IS, THERE'S NOTHING
ANYONE CAN SAY OR DO.

23:03.136 --> 23:04.771
ONLY GOD CAN HELP.

23:07.307 --> 23:09.843
GOD?

23:12.212 --> 23:15.081
HANNA ‐‐
NO, DON'T.

23:15.081 --> 23:17.918
THAT'S NOT YOU,
AND YOU KNOW IT.

23:17.918 --> 23:21.087
THAT'S NOT YOU AT ALL.

23:21.087 --> 23:24.390
WHAT I KNOW IS THAT I DON'T
KNOW WHO I AM RIGHT NOW.

23:27.160 --> 23:29.029
LISTEN, I UNDERSTAND.

23:29.029 --> 23:32.599
♪♪♪♪

23:32.599 --> 23:35.068
HAVE YOU SEEN MY PHONE?

23:35.068 --> 23:37.470
YEAH. IT'S CHARGING
HERE IN THE KITCHEN.

23:39.540 --> 23:41.808
I NEED TO CALL BENNY.

23:41.808 --> 23:51.818
♪♪♪♪

23:51.818 --> 23:58.825
♪♪♪♪

23:58.825 --> 24:04.738
♪♪♪♪

24:04.738 --> 24:06.740
[ CELLPHONE RINGS ]

24:06.740 --> 24:12.412
♪♪♪♪

24:12.412 --> 24:14.948
HELLO?
<i>HELLO?</i>

24:14.948 --> 24:16.149
MISS YOUNG.

24:16.149 --> 24:17.551
MITCH, I NEED
TO TALK WITH BENNY.

24:17.551 --> 24:20.554
<i>PUT HIM ON THE PHONE.</i>

24:20.554 --> 24:22.255
HE CAN'T COME TO THE PHONE
RIGHT NOW.

24:22.255 --> 24:23.690
WHERE IS HE?

24:23.690 --> 24:25.826
<i>HE WENT OUT</i>
<i>FOR A LITTLE BIT.</i>

24:25.826 --> 24:28.629
OKAY, WELL, TELL HIM I NEED
TO TALK TO HIM, OKAY?

24:28.629 --> 24:30.964
SURE, SURE THING,
MISS YOUNG.

24:30.964 --> 24:35.035
<i>WE GOT TO FIGURE OUT SOME</i>
<i>KIND OF FUNERAL ARRANGEMENTS.</i>

24:35.035 --> 24:36.402
OKAY. ALL RIGHT.

24:36.402 --> 24:37.804
I'LL HAVE HIM CALL YOU.

24:37.804 --> 24:39.039
<i>OKAY.</i>

24:40.574 --> 24:42.308
[ SIGHS ]

24:42.308 --> 24:50.383
♪♪♪♪

24:50.383 --> 24:52.118
I DON'T KNOW WHERE HE IS.

24:52.118 --> 24:53.987
I GUESS I GOT TO START.

24:56.422 --> 24:58.992
WITH ALL THE HELP YOU GAVE ME
WITH AMANDA,

24:58.992 --> 25:02.736
HANNA, LET ME
HELP YOU WITH THIS.

25:02.736 --> 25:04.771
I WANT TO SAY NO,

25:04.771 --> 25:07.974
I CAN'T ASK YOU
TO DO THAT, BUT...

25:07.974 --> 25:12.345
IF YOU COULD, IT WOULD
HELP ME SO MUCH.

25:12.345 --> 25:13.547
YES.

25:16.282 --> 25:18.084
WE DON'T HAVE
ANY INSURANCE.

25:20.353 --> 25:22.889
DON'T WORRY.
I'LL COVER IT.

25:25.025 --> 25:27.327
I CAN'T EVEN AFFORD
THE CASKET.

25:29.530 --> 25:32.933
AFTER ALL YOU'VE DONE
FOR ME AND MY FAMILY,

25:32.933 --> 25:34.668
YOU DON'T WORRY YOUR HEAD
ONE LITTLE MOMENT

25:34.668 --> 25:36.970
ABOUT THIS, OKAY?

25:36.970 --> 25:38.438
I WILL HELP YOU.

25:40.641 --> 25:43.610
THANK YOU.

25:43.610 --> 25:46.279
NO. THANK <i>YOU.</i>

25:46.279 --> 25:51.652
♪♪♪♪

25:51.652 --> 25:55.288
I REMEMBER WHEN
AMANDA DIED,

25:55.288 --> 25:56.723
THEY WERE ASKING
ALL THESE QUESTIONS

25:56.723 --> 25:59.159
AT THE FUNERAL HOME.

25:59.159 --> 26:03.403
"WHAT'S HER FAVORITE FLOWER?
WHAT'S HER FAVORITE COLOR?"

26:03.403 --> 26:07.440
♪♪♪♪

26:07.440 --> 26:08.842
I REMEMBER THAT.

26:11.745 --> 26:12.846
HOW DO YOU KNOW WHAT

26:12.846 --> 26:15.448
A 5‐YEAR‐OLD'S
FAVORITE FLOWER IS?

26:17.483 --> 26:19.686
JUST CHOOSE FOR HIM.

26:22.589 --> 26:26.326
[ Voice breaking ]
WELL...HE LOVED PURPLE.

26:26.326 --> 26:27.794
THAT IS HIS ‐‐

26:29.830 --> 26:33.767
...WAS HIS FAVORITE COLOR.

26:33.767 --> 26:36.336
THAT'S A START.

26:36.336 --> 26:39.039
HE LIKED TOYS.

26:39.039 --> 26:41.675
OH.

26:41.675 --> 26:44.611
I HOPE BENNY
GETS THAT...

26:44.611 --> 26:47.914
NOW, YOU JUST LET ME
HANDLE BENNY, OKAY?

26:47.914 --> 26:49.315
I'LL CALL HIM.

26:52.519 --> 26:55.255
THANK YOU.

26:55.255 --> 26:56.757
YEAH.

26:56.757 --> 26:58.859
WE'VE GOT TO GET
SOME FOOD IN YOU.

27:01.101 --> 27:04.571
I'M OKAY.
I DON'T WANT TO EAT.

27:04.571 --> 27:07.440
YES, YOU NEED TO EAT.

27:07.440 --> 27:08.809
WAIT.

27:08.809 --> 27:11.444
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

27:11.444 --> 27:12.679
YOU COOKING?

27:12.679 --> 27:14.114
YES.

27:16.049 --> 27:19.285
THEN I KNOW
I DON'T WANT NONE.

27:19.285 --> 27:20.086
HANNA?

27:20.086 --> 27:21.487
[ CHUCKLES ]

27:23.657 --> 27:26.693
IT'S OKAY.

27:26.693 --> 27:31.031
THE LAUGHTER WILL COME BACK,
AND SO WILL YOUR SMILE.

27:31.031 --> 27:36.269
AND MAYBE MY COOKING
WILL GET YOU THERE FASTER.

27:36.269 --> 27:39.873
I DON'T THINK SO.

27:39.873 --> 27:42.175
HOW DO YOU TURN
THIS THING ON?

27:54.154 --> 27:56.657
[ LAUGHTER ]

27:56.657 --> 28:04.638
♪♪♪♪

28:04.638 --> 28:12.579
♪♪♪♪

28:12.579 --> 28:13.914
HI!

28:13.914 --> 28:14.915
Charles: SYLIA?

28:14.915 --> 28:16.517
HI!

28:16.517 --> 28:17.584
WHO ARE YOU?

28:17.584 --> 28:19.319
BABY.
[ CHUCKLES ]

28:19.319 --> 28:21.622
‐I'M SYLIA.
‐AND I'M JAX.

28:21.622 --> 28:23.990
WELL, I'M CANDACE.
YOU'RE PRETTY.

28:23.990 --> 28:25.792
WHY, THANK YOU!

28:25.792 --> 28:27.460
DO YOU KNOW MY DAD?

28:27.460 --> 28:29.229
NO, I DON'T.

28:29.229 --> 28:30.664
HE'S GOING TO BE
PRESIDENT!

28:30.664 --> 28:32.298
IS THAT SO?
COME ON.

28:32.298 --> 28:34.134
DON'T BOTHER
THE NICE LADY.

28:34.134 --> 28:35.836
NO, IT'S ‐‐ IT'S OKAY.

28:35.836 --> 28:37.203
THEY'RE BEAUTIFUL.

28:37.203 --> 28:39.573
THANK YOU.
MM‐HMM.

28:39.573 --> 28:42.075
ARE YOU VOTING FOR HIM?

28:42.075 --> 28:44.477
YES. I WILL.

28:44.477 --> 28:46.980
WELL,
I WISH I COULD VOTE.

28:46.980 --> 28:48.649
I WOULD VOTE FOR HIM.

28:48.649 --> 28:50.917
WELL, YOU'LL BE ABLE TO VOTE
FOR PRESIDENT ONE DAY.

28:50.917 --> 28:52.252
ME TOO?

28:52.252 --> 28:54.320
YEAH.
YOU, TOO, JAX.

28:54.320 --> 28:56.356
NOW, GO ON.
YOU HAVE TO GO TO SCHOOL.

28:56.356 --> 28:58.424
DO WE HAVE TO?

28:58.424 --> 29:00.694
YES. GO ON.

29:00.694 --> 29:02.736
IT'S NOT SCHOOL.
IT'S A BUS.

29:02.736 --> 29:03.970
WELL,
WE'RE ON THE ROAD.

29:03.970 --> 29:06.573
I WANT TO GO
TO MY REAL SCHOOL.

29:06.573 --> 29:08.008
YOU WILL SOON, HONEY.

29:08.008 --> 29:09.543
NICE TO MEET YOU,
MISS CANDACE.

29:09.543 --> 29:11.678
[ CHUCKLES ]
YOU, TOO.

29:11.678 --> 29:12.679
HEATHER?

29:12.679 --> 29:15.315
CAN YOU TAKE THEM?

29:15.315 --> 29:16.617
I'LL SEE YOU
AFTER MY RALLY.

29:16.617 --> 29:19.352
OKAY? I'LL BE THERE
TO TUCK YOU IN.

29:19.352 --> 29:22.689
GIVE ME A HUG.
DAD LOVES YOU.

29:22.689 --> 29:25.191
‐I LOVE YOU, TOO.
‐I LOVE YOU, DAD.

29:25.191 --> 29:27.327
[ CHUCKLES ]
DAD LOVES YOU.

29:27.327 --> 29:28.695
OKAY, GO ON.

29:28.695 --> 29:36.069
♪♪♪♪

29:36.069 --> 29:37.804
SORRY. I RUSHED BACK
TO HAVE LUNCH WITH THEM.

29:37.804 --> 29:39.940
NO. FINE.

29:39.940 --> 29:42.108
NO PHOTO OPS HERE?
NO.

29:42.108 --> 29:46.146
NONE. I TAKE BEING
A FATHER VERY SERIOUSLY.

29:46.146 --> 29:48.048
I SEE THAT.

29:48.048 --> 29:49.883
I'M SORRY
THEY BOTHERED YOU.

29:49.883 --> 29:50.951
NO, IT'S OKAY.

29:50.951 --> 29:53.319
I'M JUST SURPRISED
THE SECRET SERVICE

29:53.319 --> 29:57.190
WASN'T AROUND TO STOP THEM FROM
GOING INTO A STRANGER'S ROOM.

29:57.190 --> 29:58.592
OH, NO.

29:58.592 --> 30:01.568
I LIKE THEM TO HAVE
AS MUCH NORMALCY AS POSSIBLE.

30:01.568 --> 30:03.937
IT'S GOING TO BE HARD ONCE
WE GET IN THAT WHITE HOUSE.

30:03.937 --> 30:07.574
[ CHUCKLES ]
SO CONFIDENT.

30:07.574 --> 30:09.943
WELL, THE POLLS DON'T LIE.

30:14.447 --> 30:16.282
I'M REALLY SURPRISED BY YOU.

30:16.282 --> 30:17.851
WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

30:17.851 --> 30:20.587
HOW COMFORTABLE YOU ARE.

30:20.587 --> 30:22.823
[ CHUCKLES ]

30:22.823 --> 30:24.157
WHAT DOES THAT MEAN?

30:24.157 --> 30:26.860
WELL, I RECORDED YOU
LAST NIGHT,

30:26.860 --> 30:31.297
LET YOU HEAR IT,
AND YOU DON'T CARE.

30:31.297 --> 30:35.235
DON'T TAKE MY CALM
DEMEANOR AT FACE VALUE.

30:35.235 --> 30:37.370
I'M LIKE A DUCK ON WATER ‐‐

30:37.370 --> 30:38.505
CALM ON THE SURFACE,

30:38.505 --> 30:42.275
BUT MY FEET ARE
QUICKLY PADDLING UNDERNEATH.

30:42.275 --> 30:43.409
I SEE.

30:43.409 --> 30:47.380
♪♪♪♪

30:47.380 --> 30:50.016
COME OVER.

30:50.016 --> 30:51.384
I CAN'T.

30:51.384 --> 30:53.787
COME OVER.

30:53.787 --> 30:55.388
YOU LIKE MAKING DEMANDS,
DON'T YOU?

30:55.388 --> 30:56.590
I DO.

30:56.590 --> 31:04.505
♪♪♪♪

31:04.505 --> 31:12.445
♪♪♪♪

31:12.445 --> 31:14.548
YES?

31:14.548 --> 31:16.282
CLOSE THE DOOR.

31:16.282 --> 31:18.785
I HAVE A RALLY IN
AN HOUR AND A HALF.

31:18.785 --> 31:22.022
CLOSE THE DOOR.

31:22.022 --> 31:23.356
OKAY.

31:25.626 --> 31:27.628
YOU LEARN FAST.

31:27.628 --> 31:30.731
YES. I TRY.

31:30.731 --> 31:32.766
DO <i>YOU?</i>

31:32.766 --> 31:33.800
WHAT?

31:36.036 --> 31:38.705
LEARN FAST?

31:38.705 --> 31:41.241
DEPENDS ON THE LESSON.

31:41.241 --> 31:45.345
SO THE BIGGER THE LESSON,
THE EASIER YOU LEARN?

31:45.345 --> 31:49.182
OR THE SMALLER,
IF IT'S MEMORABLE.

31:49.182 --> 31:52.152
WAIT ‐‐ WAS THAT MEANT
IN REFERENCE TO ME?

31:52.152 --> 31:55.522
YOU'RE SLOW, BUT YOU'LL ‐‐
YOU'LL CATCH ON.

31:55.522 --> 31:56.790
IF YOU'RE TRYING
TO SEDUCE ME,

31:56.790 --> 31:58.959
YOU'RE NOT GOING TO BE ABLE
TO BY INSULTING ME.

32:01.127 --> 32:04.337
THE BODY IS GOOD,
SIZE OF THE ENGINE'S GREAT.

32:04.337 --> 32:07.708
IT'S JUST, THE SEATS
HAVEN'T BEEN BROKEN IN YET.

32:07.708 --> 32:08.842
YOU WANT TO EXPLAIN?

32:11.244 --> 32:14.681
YOU KNOW WHAT YOU'RE DOING.
YOU JUST NEED SOME WORK.

32:14.681 --> 32:17.217
WELL,
WILL YOU TEACH ME?

32:17.217 --> 32:19.553
YEAH, I'LL TEACH YOU.

32:19.553 --> 32:20.687
THANK YOU.

32:23.056 --> 32:25.191
CAN'T BELIEVE YOU.

32:25.191 --> 32:27.427
WHAT?

32:27.427 --> 32:29.730
HOW UNFAZED YOU ARE BY ME.

32:29.730 --> 32:30.931
WHY IS THAT?

32:33.366 --> 32:36.036
ARE YOU A THREAT TO ME?

32:36.036 --> 32:38.438
NO, I'M NOT A THREAT TO YOU.

32:38.438 --> 32:41.241
YEAH. I KNOW.

32:41.241 --> 32:43.476
YOU KNOW?

32:43.476 --> 32:45.178
CONFIDENCE AGAIN.

32:47.347 --> 32:50.283
ALTHOUGH, YOU DID
SCREW UP MY DAY.

32:50.283 --> 32:52.352
HONEY, ALL I DID
WAS SCREW YOUR NIGHT.

32:52.352 --> 32:54.187
THAT'S WHAT I MEAN.

32:54.187 --> 32:57.290
YOU'VE BEEN ON MY MIND
ALL DAY.

32:57.290 --> 32:59.392
I HAVE THAT KIND
OF EFFECT ON MEN.

32:59.392 --> 33:02.503
YEAH, I MEAN, I WAS TRYING
TO GIVE A SPEECH,

33:02.503 --> 33:07.634
AND ALL I COULD SEE...
TASTE...WAS YOU.

33:09.510 --> 33:11.845
THEN THE MAGIC IS WORKING.

33:11.845 --> 33:14.214
ALL TOO WELL.

33:14.214 --> 33:15.348
THANK YOU.

33:15.348 --> 33:16.817
SURE.

33:20.020 --> 33:24.224
YOU KNOW, THAT'S THE MOST FUN
I'VE HAD IN A LONG TIME.

33:24.224 --> 33:25.258
OH, YEAH?

33:25.258 --> 33:26.560
YEAH.

33:26.560 --> 33:29.162
HMM.

33:29.162 --> 33:32.465
WE'LL HAVE A LOT
MORE FUN TONIGHT.

33:32.465 --> 33:34.234
YOU PROMISE?

33:34.234 --> 33:36.703
YEAH.

33:36.703 --> 33:39.840
I THINK IT'S GOING
TO GET REALLY FUN.

33:39.840 --> 33:41.174
DO YOU?

33:41.174 --> 33:43.510
OH, YEAH.

33:43.510 --> 33:48.148
WELL, IT'S NOT YOUR DECISION,
BECAUSE I'M IN CONTROL HERE.

33:48.148 --> 33:50.551
YEAH. THAT'S RIGHT.

33:50.551 --> 33:53.153
YOU HAVE THE RECORDING.

33:53.153 --> 33:57.057
NO,
I...GAVE THEM TO YOU.

33:57.057 --> 33:59.159
ALL OF THE COPIES?

33:59.159 --> 34:01.535
ALL OF THEM.

34:01.535 --> 34:03.804
WELL, THANK YOU.

34:03.804 --> 34:06.339
WHAT'S THE THANKS FOR?

34:06.339 --> 34:09.275
FOR NOT DOING ANYTHING
WITH WHAT YOU HAVE.

34:09.275 --> 34:12.879
I WASN'T
GOING TO DO ANYTHING.

34:12.879 --> 34:17.984
WELL, IF YOU ARE,
NOW WOULD BE THE TIME.

34:17.984 --> 34:19.419
I'M NOT THE TYPE OF GUY
TO WAIT AROUND

34:19.419 --> 34:21.021
FOR THE OTHER SHOE TO DROP.

34:23.724 --> 34:25.759
LET'S DROP SOME SHOES
RIGHT NOW.

34:27.861 --> 34:29.029
OKAY.

34:32.365 --> 34:34.000
TAKE OFF YOUR CLOTHES.

34:34.000 --> 34:37.070
[ CHUCKLES ]
CANDACE.

34:37.070 --> 34:39.372
I'M NOT GOING
TO TELL YOU AGAIN.

34:39.372 --> 34:41.474
TAKE OFF YOUR CLOTHES ‐‐
NOW.

34:41.474 --> 34:42.676
CANDACE ‐‐

34:44.878 --> 34:46.312
OKAY.

34:46.312 --> 34:48.014
BUT THIS ‐‐

34:48.014 --> 34:50.116
CAN I SAY SOMETHING FIRST?

34:50.116 --> 34:54.087
I DO THE TALKING,
NOT YOU.

34:54.087 --> 34:57.490
OKAY, BUT YOU MIGHT
WANT TO HEAR THIS.

34:57.490 --> 34:58.859
IT AFFECTS YOU.

34:58.859 --> 35:01.001
DON'T TELL ME
YOU HAVE AN STD?

35:01.001 --> 35:02.168
[ CHUCKLES ]

35:02.168 --> 35:05.171
NO. NOT AT ALL.

35:05.171 --> 35:06.607
WELL, THEN,
I'M NOT INTERESTED IN HEARING

35:06.607 --> 35:08.174
ANYTHING YOU HAVE TO SAY.

35:08.174 --> 35:14.380
♪♪♪♪

35:14.380 --> 35:16.382
OFF. NOW.

35:19.686 --> 35:20.754
TAKE IT OFF.

35:20.754 --> 35:30.597
♪♪♪♪

35:30.597 --> 35:32.232
GOTTA DO MY BELT.

35:32.232 --> 35:33.266
OH, YEAH.

35:33.266 --> 35:40.240
♪♪♪♪

35:40.240 --> 35:47.180
♪♪♪♪

35:47.180 --> 35:54.154
♪♪♪♪

35:54.154 --> 35:55.922
THERE YOU ARE.

35:58.191 --> 36:02.703
I KNEW YOU COULDN'T RESIST.

36:02.703 --> 36:06.406
YEAH, WELL, I AM A SUCKER
FOR A PRETTY FACE.

36:06.406 --> 36:08.474
IN THE BED.

36:08.474 --> 36:09.943
NOW.

36:09.943 --> 36:11.311
WAIT FOR ME.

36:11.311 --> 36:20.153
♪♪♪♪

36:20.153 --> 36:24.190
♪♪♪♪

36:29.896 --> 36:32.733
♪♪♪♪

36:32.733 --> 36:36.302
LOOK. LOOK, LOOK.

36:36.302 --> 36:40.106
YOU'VE HAD ME SITTING
IN HERE ALL NIGHT LONG.

36:40.106 --> 36:41.141
HAVE I?

36:41.141 --> 36:43.076
YES.

36:43.076 --> 36:45.211
NOW, IF YOU WANTED TO ARREST ME,
YOU'D HAVE DONE IT.

36:45.211 --> 36:46.913
OH, SO YOU'RE NOT
GOING TO TALK TO US?

36:46.913 --> 36:49.082
NO!

36:49.082 --> 36:52.586
OH, THAT'S WHY YOU'VE BEEN
SITTING HERE ALL NIGHT?

36:52.586 --> 36:54.921
OKAY. FINE.

36:54.921 --> 36:57.624
YOU'RE NOT UNDER ARREST.

36:57.624 --> 36:59.793
THEN WHY THE HELL AM I HERE?

36:59.793 --> 37:00.900
WE BROUGHT YOU IN
FOR QUESTIONING.

37:00.900 --> 37:01.901
AW, MAN!

37:01.901 --> 37:04.270
HEY, I DID. I DID.
NO, YOU ‐‐

37:04.270 --> 37:06.840
YO, YOU SAID
I WAS UNDER ARREST.

37:06.840 --> 37:08.942
YOU SAID THAT TO ME.
NO, WE DIDN'T.

37:08.942 --> 37:11.177
WE ASKED YOU TO COME DOWN
FOR QUESTIONING.

37:11.177 --> 37:12.746
ALL RIGHT, WELL, I'M GETTING
THE HELL OUT OF HERE.

37:12.746 --> 37:14.447
NOT SO FAST.

37:14.447 --> 37:15.849
NOT SO FAST?

37:15.849 --> 37:17.951
IF I'M NOT UNDER ARREST,
YOU CAN'T HOLD ME HERE.

37:17.951 --> 37:21.287
LEGALLY, I CAN'T ‐‐
ALL RIGHT. THEN I'M WALKING.

37:21.287 --> 37:23.289
MR. YOUNG,
HAVE A SEAT.

37:23.289 --> 37:25.325
WHO THE HELL IS THIS?
WHO THE HELL ARE YOU?

37:25.325 --> 37:27.460
I'M AGENT DAVIS.
AGENT DAVIS.

37:27.460 --> 37:28.729
AND WHAT DO YOU WANT?

37:28.729 --> 37:29.763
YOUR DNA.

37:29.763 --> 37:31.798
[ Chuckling ]
WHAT? WHAT? FOR WHAT?

37:31.798 --> 37:33.033
WE NEED TO RUN
SOME TESTS.

37:33.033 --> 37:34.768
NO. I'M NOT GIVING
YOU MY DNA, MAN.

37:34.768 --> 37:35.902
YOU AIN'T GETTING
NO BLOOD FROM ME.

37:35.902 --> 37:37.270
SEE, THAT'S WHERE
YOU'RE WRONG.

37:37.270 --> 37:39.706
NO, I'M NOT WRONG,
'CAUSE I HAVE RIGHTS.

37:39.706 --> 37:40.874
YES, YOU DO.

37:40.874 --> 37:42.676
BUT WE HAVE REASON TO BELIEVE
YOU ARE A THREAT

37:42.676 --> 37:44.811
TO THE NATIONAL SECURITY
OF A PRESIDENTIAL CANDIDATE.

37:44.811 --> 37:46.112
WHAT?

37:47.848 --> 37:49.816
YES.
WE NEED YOUR DNA.

37:49.816 --> 37:51.284
YO, I'M NOT ‐‐
I'M NOT GIVING ‐‐

37:51.284 --> 37:53.353
AND YOU CAN GIVE IT
TO US WILLINGLY,

37:53.353 --> 37:54.487
OR WE CAN TAKE IT.

37:54.487 --> 37:56.189
WHAT THE HELL
IS GOING ON HERE?

37:56.189 --> 37:57.390
YOU NEED TO TELL ME
THAT, OKAY?

37:57.390 --> 38:00.193
I DON'T KNOW
NO PRESIDENTIAL CANDIDATE.

38:00.193 --> 38:01.201
DNA, SIR.

38:01.201 --> 38:03.870
NO, AND I DIDN'T
THREATEN NOBODY!

38:03.870 --> 38:05.739
OKAY.
OKAY, WHAT?

38:05.739 --> 38:07.273
BE RIGHT BACK.

38:07.273 --> 38:10.343
SO, I SIT HERE MORE NOW, RIGHT?
NO FOOD, NO WATER?

38:10.343 --> 38:13.747
I JUST SIT HERE
'CAUSE YOU SAY SO?

38:13.747 --> 38:15.415
JUST RELAX.
RELAX.

38:15.415 --> 38:16.850
EASY FOR YOU TO SAY.

38:16.850 --> 38:18.785
♪♪♪♪

38:21.054 --> 38:25.425
♪♪♪♪

38:25.425 --> 38:27.561
CANDACE...

38:27.561 --> 38:29.830
WHAT?

38:29.830 --> 38:31.164
YOU CAN'T DO THAT.

38:31.164 --> 38:33.399
WELL, I JUST DID.

38:33.399 --> 38:35.569
AND I TAKE SELFIES, TOO.

38:37.403 --> 38:39.105
[ GIGGLES ]

38:39.105 --> 38:41.575
YOU DON'T RESPECT ME,
DO YOU?

38:41.575 --> 38:42.943
WHAT?

38:42.943 --> 38:45.979
I MEAN, RESPECT FOR WHAT
I'VE ACCOMPLISHED?

38:45.979 --> 38:47.347
I'M GOING TO BE
THE YOUNGEST PRESIDENT

38:47.347 --> 38:48.549
EVER ELECTED TO OFFICE.

38:48.549 --> 38:51.417
WELL, THAT'S GOOD.

38:51.417 --> 38:54.087
NO. NO, YOU DON'T
RESPECT ME.

38:54.087 --> 38:56.456
YOU DON'T.

38:56.456 --> 38:59.926
I RESPECT THE OFFICE,

38:59.926 --> 39:02.035
BUT YOU'RE HUMAN,

39:02.035 --> 39:05.205
JUST LIKE EVERYONE ELSE,
AND IF I CUT YOU, YOU BLEED.

39:07.173 --> 39:09.976
SO IS THAT WHY THE PHONE
AND RECORDING?

39:12.178 --> 39:15.281
WHY ARE YOU SO...TRUSTING?

39:16.950 --> 39:19.520
I'VE ALWAYS BEEN THAT WAY.

39:19.520 --> 39:20.787
IT'S NOT GOOD.

39:23.356 --> 39:27.293
SO, YOU'RE SAVING THIS UP
TO MAKE ME BLEED?

39:27.293 --> 39:30.230
A GIRL ALWAYS NEEDS
SOMETHING FOR A RAINY DAY.

39:32.799 --> 39:35.168
BUT I'M GOING TO BE
PRESIDENT.

39:35.168 --> 39:36.202
MM‐HMM.

39:36.202 --> 39:39.272
AND THAT'S ALL THE POWER
IN THE WORLD.

39:39.272 --> 39:43.109
AND THAT'S ALL THE POWER
TO HOLD AGAINST YOU.

39:43.109 --> 39:44.377
I DON'T LIKE
BEING BLACKMAILED.

39:44.377 --> 39:46.179
I'M NOT GOING TO
BLACKMAIL YOU.

39:46.179 --> 39:48.982
OR THE THOUGHT OF IT.

39:48.982 --> 39:50.250
DON'T THINK ABOUT IT.

39:50.250 --> 39:52.653
JUST...
THINK ABOUT ALL THIS.

39:52.653 --> 39:53.820
STOP IT.

39:57.090 --> 39:58.725
WHY ARE YOU SO SERIOUS?

39:58.725 --> 40:00.193
YOU SAY THAT
AS IF YOU KNOW ME.

40:00.193 --> 40:02.636
I DO KNOW ‐‐
NO.

40:05.038 --> 40:10.176
YOU HAVE NO IDEA
WHO OR WHAT I AM.

40:13.614 --> 40:18.051
I'M SENATOR
CHARLES WALTER FREDERICKSON.

40:18.051 --> 40:19.686
I'M AWARE OF THAT.

40:23.690 --> 40:27.260
YOU DON'T THINK
THIS IS SERIOUS?

40:27.260 --> 40:31.665
OKAY, WELL...
LET'S GET SERIOUS.

40:33.934 --> 40:36.236
VINCENT, I NEED YOU.

40:38.038 --> 40:39.105
WHO'S VINCENT?

40:39.105 --> 40:45.111
♪♪♪♪

40:45.111 --> 40:46.947
WHAT THE HELL
IS GOING ON?!

40:46.947 --> 40:48.915
THIS IS ILLEGAL!

40:48.915 --> 40:50.651
Agent: WE'VE REASON TO BELIEVE
THAT YOU'VE BEEN WORKING

40:50.651 --> 40:53.820
WITH A COUNTER CELL IN SYRIA
RECRUITING AMERICANS FOR JIHAD.

40:53.820 --> 40:55.055
WHAT?!

40:55.055 --> 40:56.557
YOU'RE IN VIOLATION
OF THE PATRIOT ACT.

40:56.557 --> 40:58.358
WHAT ARE YOU
TALKING ABOUT?

40:58.358 --> 40:59.693
WE CHECKED
YOUR COMPUTER.

40:59.693 --> 41:00.934
Agent #2: WE HAVE IT.

41:00.934 --> 41:02.569
THAT IS NOT MINE!

41:02.569 --> 41:04.538
YOU'RE UNDER ARREST
FOR TERRORISM.

41:04.538 --> 41:09.042
♪♪♪♪

41:09.042 --> 41:11.077
LOOK AT ME.

41:11.077 --> 41:13.614
LOOK AT ME.

41:15.949 --> 41:17.283
YOU'RE UNDER ARREST.

41:20.554 --> 41:22.889
I'M NOT THE MOTHER...
TO PLAY THESE GAMES WITH.

41:22.889 --> 41:27.327
♪♪♪♪

41:27.327 --> 41:28.461
NEXT...
WHAT WOULD YOU LIKE US

41:28.461 --> 41:29.630
TO DO, SIR?

41:29.630 --> 41:31.064
<i>...ON "THE HAVES</i>
<i>AND THE HAVE NOTS"...</i>

41:31.064 --> 41:33.600
THAT LAST GIRL?
YEAH, SHE GOT LIFE, SIR.

41:33.600 --> 41:36.336
YOU DO NOT WANT TO DIE.
YOU WANT TO LIVE.

41:36.336 --> 41:37.571
AND YOU WANT TO LIVE WELL,

41:37.571 --> 41:39.973
BE A GOOD MOTHER
TO THIS CHILD.

41:39.973 --> 41:42.175
YOU WERE GONE, AND I
COULDN'T EVEN LOOK FOR YOU,

41:42.175 --> 41:43.677
BECAUSE I WAS IN JAIL!

41:43.677 --> 41:45.812
I KNOW.
I PUT YOU THERE.

41:45.812 --> 41:47.247
YOU WERE AN ESCORT,
AND YOU BLACKMAILED

41:47.247 --> 41:48.715
SEVERAL HIGH‐PROFILE MEN,

41:48.715 --> 41:51.151
AND YOU'RE WANTED RIGHT NOW
FOR QUESTIONING IN A MURDER.

41:51.151 --> 41:52.986
YOU'RE A POWDER KEG
WAITING FOR A SPARK.

41:52.986 --> 41:55.155
VERONICA, WHAT DO YOU
WANT FROM ME?

41:55.155 --> 41:57.357
I KNOW I PUT IT ON YOU,
BUT THIS IS CRAZY.
